    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Jackson Merrill** serving as the undeniable cornerstone of the lineup. With a robust 75.10 score, he benefits from a highly favorable matchup against Feltner (xERA 4.63) in a hitter-friendly park that yields a 14% efficiency boost. Alongside him, **Drake Baldwin** remains a high-floor selection (61.45) batting second against Cavalli, where the combination of prime lineup positioning and a favorable park environment offsets his neutral platoon status. While **Kyle Tucker** and **Heliot Ramos** face difficult assignments against elite arms like Logan Webb and Tyler Glasnow, their high-level talent and the stolen base potential against slow-delivery pitchers keeps their scores competitive enough to warrant starts despite the SP skill penalties.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Josh Jung**, who narrowly missed the cut with a 41.26 score. While his potential is undeniable, his matchup against Bubba Chandler was hampered by a 19% SP skill penalty and the uncertainty surrounding his lineup spot; the optimizer opted for the higher-floor upside of **Dominic Smith** and **Nasim Nunez** to fill gaps in the infield. We are also monitoring the lineup status of **Marcell Ozuna**, who faces a daunting assignment against Jacob deGrom. His score of 44.24 is heavily reliant on his assumed cleanup spot, and any shift down the order could necessitate a pivot. We continue to manage our roster depth carefully, with **Gunnar Henderson**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, and **Jordan Westburg** currently unavailable, forcing us to lean heavily on the remaining active pool. Managers should be particularly wary of the matchups for **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Andy Pages**, as their scoring potential has been significantly compressed by the high-skill profiles of their opposing starters.",
